@node "Introduction" "Introduction"
 What is THIS !?

Well, this program makes your life easier if you are a big Manga fan like I am
^_^.

I have a whole bunch of Manga-Images that I collected via InterNET. All of them
has such strange names like "9mj-001.gif" or "smpc012.png".  Now this program
makes use of the well-known feature of AmigaOS (YEAH!):  The File-Comment

It loads a @{"configuration" link "Configuration" 0} file with all the short acronyms and full names of the
series.  Then it tries to search through this database for your specified file.
If it's found, it will comment the file with the full description and the
number of the picture.

   "smpc012.png" gets the comment "Sailor-Moon Picture-Card #12"

"WHOW ! This is incredible !" - But this isn't everything !!! It is also able
to comment unknown pictures by separating the numbers from the filename (It
tries to ^_^)

It will comment "asa101.jpg" as "Asa #101". Nice, isn't it ? ^_^
@endnode

@node "How To Use" "How To Use"
Easy ... type "MangaCom <configfile> <picture>

 Example:

      - MangaCom S:Mangas.cfg MANGA:3x3/sazan1.gif
        This will try to comment the picture sazan1.gif with the
        help of the Mangas.cfg database.

      - MangaCom SYS:Prefs/Presets/Mangas.cfg ranma12.jpg
        This comments only this Ranma 1/2 picture inside the current
        directory.

      - MangaCom
        This does nothing except printing out a simple copyright-text.

      - MangaCom ?
        This shows you a short USAGE-text.
@endnode

@node "Configuration" "Configuration"
 How to use the Config-File:
 That's easy ...

 Here some examples :

 mrg2_           -/- MRG-II
 (koi|mystic)    -/- Mystic-Princess Koi Hime
 Cjr             -/- Cjiro
 tw(%|i)nd(%|ol) -/- Twin-Dolls
 M(a___|7)       -/- Macross-7

 <-------------> <-> <----------------------------------------->
 @{i}FILENAME@{ui}     @{i}SEPARATOR@{ui}       @{i}COMPLETE DESCRIPTION@{ui}

Write the filename and the description separated by the "@{b}-/-@{ub}" symbol.

Nukunuku*        -/- Super-Cultural CatGirl Nuku-Nuku

Delete the picture-number from the filename because MangaCom will get the
number for you.  The filename-search is case insensitive, so you don't have to
worry about upper/lowercase chars.
@endnode

@node "Bugs" "Bugs"
The AmigaE-rewritten code gave me some nice bugs like crashes when loading an
empty database.  I fixed everything as good as I could by using Enforcer. But
if you find some, then @{"contact" link "Author" 0} me !!!
@endnode

@node "History" "History"
v0.x    AREXX-TIME
        A simple AREXX-Script !!!
        VEEEEEEEEEEERY slow !!!


v1.0    START

        My first attempt to write the EXE-version.
        Very simple commandline-parser.


v1.1    UPDATE

        CLI-parser more complex.
        Implemented the '?' help-text.
        Implemented HD/Path recognition


v1.2    UPDATE / BUGFIX

        Batch-Processing (MangaCom <file1> <file2>...) is
        finished. FINALLY !!!
        Fixed Number-Bug.


v1.3    BUGFIX

        Unknown files are handled more precisely.
        Number-Separator works correct now.

v1.4    BUGFIX

        Rewrote the whole File-Parsing routine.
        Implemented the -> " <- char recognition for the filename.
        Checked out several routines and cleaned up the code.

v1.5    RELEASE

        FIRST PUBLIC RELEASE

v1.6b   UPDATE

        I tried to implement wildcard-checking to the db-parser.
        ... and I failed ^_-

v1.99b  REWRITTEN

        I kicked Blitz2 and ported the complete code over to AmigaE.
        As result I got a smaller EXE. (15.320 KBytes smaller !!)
        Speeded up the db-scanner.
        Added full DOS-Wildcard support for the db-scanner.
        First parameter is now the db-file and the second the picture.
        For this reason I didn't include a batch-mode like in v1.5
        (look at To-Do!).

v2.0    RELEASE

        SECOND PUBLIC RELEASE
@endnode

@node "Future" "Future"

                  -------- ???????????????? --------

This  is  the  best program ever done.  Why should there be an update ? Well,
maybe I forgot to implement some bugs ^_^

Please  tell  me what you would like to see. If you want some specific routines
and you have the idea how to code them, then feel free to send me your
incredible idea by @{"eMail" link "Author" 0} !

Until now I only want to ...

 ... include DOS-Wildcards for the picture-names in the Shell
 ... add some more AI to the Unknown-Name scanner.
 ... translate this document into German, Italian and Japanese. ^_-
 ... remove more mistakes I wrote in this document.
 ... write some more bugs to find ^_^.

I tested this tool on my Amiga 1230-882/50MhZ and 16 MB of FastRAM together
with Enforcer. Send me a note if it (still?) crashes :P
@endnode

